{"type":"message","id":"627e8702","parentId":"f0d0be0c","timestamp":"2026-05-29T09:10:17.763Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The push is timing out because GitHub seems unreachable from this machine (or very slow). The local repo has the May 29 commit, but it can't push.\n\nLet me check: the `/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone` was cloned from GitHub. The `git log origin/main` showed the latest was May 28. But when I did `git log --oneline` (without origin/main) it showed May 29 at the top. This means the May 29 commit exists locally in the clone but hasn't been pushed to GitHub yet.\n\nSo the situation is:\n- May 29 commit exists locally in `/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone` (commit 03ded9a)\n\n\n- GitHub origin has May 28 (commit 1046fe7) - so the May 29 commit needs to be pushed\n- Network to GitHub is blocked or extremely slow\n\nI should verify whether the local clone might be incomplete or missing the May 29 files, and I should probably explore an alternative push method rather than continuing to wait on the timeout.\n\nLooking at what happened: the backup script ran `git pull origin main` then `rsync` added files, committed, and tried to push. But the push failed with that HTTP/2 error. So the commit exists locally but never made it to GitHub. I could try pushing over SSH or HTTPS with a different port, or check if there's a cached credential that might work, but first let me verify if the 03ded9a commit actually contains the workspace files we need.\n","thinkingSignature":"a04e8ce6db7739edad7e45a27266b3cf39a8a9a07898a771da8acf3b82ba84c6"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lzuiks9i0iew_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git -C /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone show --stat 03ded9a 2>/dev/null | tail -10","timeout":8}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":282,"output":380,"cacheRead":60141,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":60803,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite"