{"type":"message","id":"dbca2185","parentId":"6892ea21","timestamp":"2026-05-29T09:10:41.725Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The commit 03ded9a is there with 22352 files. The issue is that the local repo has the commit but it hasn't been pushed to origin yet (because the push timed out). The push keeps timing out. Let me try to push with a shorter timeout or try a different approach.\n\nActually wait - looking back at the log: \"fatal: HTTP/2 stream 1 was not closed cleanly\" - this error came from the backup script which ran at 03:05. But the log also says \"Backup pushed to GitHub\" right after. That seems contradictory.\n\nLet me check if maybe the push actually succeeded despite the error message, or if the error happened during fetch.\n \nThe fatal error appears after a git add -A and git commit, which suggests the push itself failed at the network level even though the commit was created locally. The commit existing in the local repo doesn't mean it made it to GitHub yet - that push consistently times out.\n\nI'm seeing two separate problems: network connectivity to GitHub is timing out, and there's a local commit (03ded9a) that hasn't been pushed. I should try using the GitHub CLI instead since the machine has credentials configured there, which might handle the connection more reliably than a direct git push.\n","thinkingSignature":"adc451bbcac8fd59875a11f9dfb03f91cd8c6f0ffecadbf30412b664aa98e9fd"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_65a0n5qdi0h4_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"gh auth status 2>&1 | head -10","timeout":10}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":328,"output":304,"cacheRead":60420,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61052,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780045827393,"responseId":"06688b04ead0818c2606816947664cc3"}}
