{"type":"message","id":"7c300606","parentId":"066457d5","timestamp":"2026-05-29T09:11:04.812Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"GitHub authentication is fine. The issue is that the git push is hanging - likely a network connectivity issue to GitHub from this machine. The local clone has the commit 03ded9a with the May 29 backup, but it can't push it.\n\nLet me try a different approach - use `gh` to push via the GitHub API instead of git. Or alternatively, I could try to understand why git push hangs and potentially fix the network issue.\n\nActually, let me think about what the user originally said - \"没看到，只有28号的\". They looked at GitHub and only see May 28 backup. This could mean:\n\n\n1. The May 29 commit exists locally but the push to GitHub failed (despite the log saying it succeeded - that was likely a false positive)\n2. The push started but then hung and was killed before actually completing\n\nThe log entry said \"Backup pushed to GitHub\" at 03:05:11, but the commit 03ded9a is timestamped 03:04. If the push actually failed silently, the local commit might never have made it to the remote, even though the log claimed success.\n\nThe git process was killed by SIGKILL, likely from a timeout. But the log also shows a fatal network error about the HTTP/2 stream being closed improperly. This suggests the push hung and then was forcefully terminated, but the script continued and reported success anyway - a false positive. The commit never actually reached GitHub.\n\nI need to figure out how to actually push this commit. Let me try using `ghapi` or explore alternative approaches, though direct Git operations are probably the most straightforward path forward.\n","thinkingSignature":"b10a7cb5ab26cce6a5f9f368c2d1b73f2921f6eb6a09f050bfc099377db1e1b8"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_9avue8u0b291_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cd /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone && git push https://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@github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup.git main --force 2>&1 &\nGPID=$!\nfor i in $(seq 1 20); do\n  sleep 1\n  if ! kill -0 $GPID 2>/dev/null; then\n    echo \"DONE exit=$?\"\n    break\n  fi\n  echo -n \".\"\ndone\nif kill -0 $GPID 2>/dev/null; then\n  kill $GPID 2>/dev/null\n  echo \" TIMEOUT\"\nfi","timeout":25}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":109,"output":526,"cacheRead":60745,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61380,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780045843938,"responseId":"06688b1442e05b86f6fb6141c1a2b2ed"}}
