{"type":"message","id":"d16e2459","parentId":"b1512360","timestamp":"2026-05-29T09:11:38.871Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The git push is timing out, which suggests a network issue to GitHub. But the local repo has commit 03ded9a from today. The push failed in the backup script too - it eventually said \"pushed\" but the local and remote have diverged.\n\nLet me check - when the backup script ran `git push`, did it succeed or was the commit 03ded9a only local?\n\nActually, looking at the backup script - it runs `git add .` → `git commit` → `git push`. The log shows it pushed and sent a Feishu notification. But when I run `git fetch origin main` it only shows up to 1046fe7 (May 28). \n\nThis discrepancy suggests the push didn't actually succeed. The backup script's `git pull` before starting might have caused issues if there was a conflict. But looking at the log output more carefully, there's a fatal HTTP error followed by a backup pushed notification and Feishu message being sent - so the script is indicating success even though the push appears to have failed.\n\nThe sequence shows the pull succeeded, the commit was created locally, but the push failed with a network error. Yet the script continued and reported success, meaning the notification was sent without the commit actually reaching GitHub. There's a timing mismatch where the commit was made at 03:04 but the log shows the push failing, yet somehow the script proceeded as if it worked.\n\nThis points to the local repo being out of sync with what's actually on GitHub—the commit exists locally but never made it to the remote. The user's confusion about only seeing May 28's backup matches what I'm finding: the May 29 commit is only present locally, not pushed. I need to get that commit to GitHub, but my network access seems blocked, so the commit is essentially stranded.\n","thinkingSignature":"48834c4cc33f31b1f2953a0abeef673019fc823c939a7761ae287a7cd5e95a73"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n情况已经清楚了：\n\n**本地有 5月29日 的备份**（commit `03ded9a`），但因为 push 时网络报错（HTTP/2 stream 不完整），导致这个 commit 实际上没有成功推送到 GitHub。你看到的只是 5月28日 的备份。\n\n问题：你的机器访问 GitHub 非常慢，push 会超时。备份脚本当时报 \"pushed\" 是误报——脚本没有正确判断 push 是否真的成功。\n\n**解决方案**：\n\n1. **你手动触发一次 push** —— 直接在你机器上跑：\n   ```bash\n   cd /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone && git push origin main --force\n   ```\n   或者\n\n2. **换个时间再试** —— 凌晨 03:00 网络可能更稳定，今晚看看能不能正常 push\n\n需要我帮你把 backup log 的错误判断修复一下吗？"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62,"output":559,"cacheRead":61089,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":61710,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780045881127,"responseId":"06688b391085b715dc9c581bb47909b4"}}
