{"type":"message","id":"6f7a3ca6","parentId":"499f9aa1","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:21:10.779Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I see the issue. The backup script has two categories:\n\n1. `OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/` → goes to `workspace-tts/` in backup\n2. `HOME/workspace-tts/` → goes to `workspace-tts/` in backup\n\nBut `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` doesn't exist (confirmed). And `~/workspace-tts/` also exists.\n\nWait, but the backup shows `workspace-tts` exists in the backup at `/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/2026-05-29/workspace-tts/`... but actually earlier `ls /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/2026-05-29/ | grep tts` returned nothing. Let me double-check.\n\n\nActually, looking back at the output, `workspace-tts` wasn't in the list of backed up directories—only the others were there. The backup script is trying to sync from both `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` and `~/workspace-tts/`, but neither source appears to have actually made it into the backup, which is odd.\n\nLet me look at the rsync function more carefully. The function takes a source path and a destination path within the date directory. When `do_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"` is called, it should be mapping the contents of `~/workspace-tts/` directly to `workspace-tts/` in the backup, not inside another workspace folder. So if the backup is showing it as `workspace/workspace-tts/`, that suggests something else might be creating that nested structure, or I'm misreading how the destination path is being constructed.\n\nBut the actual backup output shows `workspace-tts` at the top level, not nested. So I need to figure out what actually got backed up versus what I expected.\n\nThe issue is that `HOME/workspace-tts/` points to `~/workspace-tts/` which exists, but the backup script doesn't have a corresponding `do_rsync` call for `HOME/workspace-tts/` — only `OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/`. Since `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` doesn't exist, nothing gets backed up from that path.\n\nYet the backup shows `workspace-tts/` at the root level, so it must have come from somewhere. If `rsync` is copying the directory itself rather than its contents, then `do_rsync(\"$HOME/workspace-tts/\", \"workspace-tts/\")` would create `workspace-tts/` inside the date directory, which matches what I'm seeing. But the script doesn't actually have that line, so I'm confused about where this is coming from.\n\nLet me trace through the backup source more carefully. The `workspace-tts` at the root level of `/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/2026-05-29/` could be from either `OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/` or `HOME/workspace-tts/`, but neither source actually exists on the system. And `ls /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/2026-05-29/ | grep tts` returned nothing, so something doesn't add up. I think I was looking at the wrong directory listing earlier—the `workspace-tts` I saw was actually under the main `workspace/` folder, not at the root level of the backup.\n\nSo the actual structure is: root level has `workspace/`, `workspace-content/`, `workspace-director/`, etc., but `workspace-tts/` doesn't exist at the root. This means the `do_rsync(\"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\", \"workspace-tts/\")` call failed because that source directory doesn't exist. The backup script tries to sync `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` which is empty, and `~/workspace-tts/` which is a separate directory that doesn't get backed up to the location the user expects.\n\nTo fix this, I need to modify the backup script to add `do_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"` so that `~/workspace-tts/` actually gets included in the backup. Before I make that change, I should verify whether the user wants me to update the backup script, and then I can re-run the backup to confirm the fix works.\n\nLet me check the current backup script and add the missing line, then re-execute the backup to populate the correct directory.\n","thinkingSignature":"5b5183f2377a9609e25b5fd3f161a4a50f47d1836b5c24e9cf2fff9f36aef799"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到了。备份脚本里 `workspace-tts` 源路径配置错了：\n\n```bash\n# 当前脚本 - 源路径不存在\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"\n\n# 实际 tts 的 workspace 在 HOME 下\n# ~/workspace-tts/ 存在，但脚本没有备份它\n```\n\n所以 `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` 是空的，`~/workspace-tts/` 才是真正的内容，但脚本没有备份它。\n\n我来修复备份脚本，然后重新备份：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_fvqufly8zlqm_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"cat -n ~/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh | grep -n \"workspace-tts\\|workspace-main\\|workspace-agent\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":371,"output":1076,"cacheRead":63964,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65411,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780057260458,"responseId":"0668b7ac6d9bc5f651bfdf7479f7a5cc"}}
