{"type":"message","id":"c78c6611","parentId":"98d04041","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:21:16.873Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Looking at the backup script more carefully:\n- `OPENCLAW_DIR` = `$HOME/.openclaw` = `/home/halei/.openclaw`\n- The script backs up:  - `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` → `workspace-tts/` (inside DATE_DIR)\n  - The main workspace has `workspace/` → `workspace/` (inside DATE_DIR) which contains `workspace-tts` subfolder\n  \nBut wait - the backup is at `/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/2026-05-29/workspace-tts/` and the path we checked was `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/`. These are DIFFERENT locations.\n\nThe backup script does:\n- `do_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"` → copies to `$DATE_DIR/workspace-tts/`\n\n\n- But when I checked `ls /tmp/openclaw-backup-clone/2026-05-29/ | grep tts` it returned nothing\n\nI need to verify whether the source `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` actually exists.\n","thinkingSignature":"e1853b0c1a4fc15170249e852197275188a8f714241d49c8aab0e31ef9023a4c"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_lczrdf7mju3x_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-tts/ 2>/dev/null | head -5; echo \"exists: $?\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":152,"output":292,"cacheRead":64332,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64776,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780057271085,"responseId":"0668b7b7335e7ea08a1c16dc7076e073"}}
