{"type":"message","id":"0fc11c14","parentId":"65fe67b1","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:21:24.247Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"It exists! But it wasn't being backed up. The path is `$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/` = `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-tts/`. But when I checked `~/.openclaw/`, the workspace-tts wasn't listed. Let me check again.\n\nWait, earlier I ran `ls -la ~/.openclaw/ | grep workspace` and only saw `workspace` and `workspace-archive-e-commerce`. But the directory exists at `/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-tts/`? That's contradictory.\n\nLet me re-check - maybe my earlier command was wrong. The earlier command was `ls -la ~/.openclaw/ | grep workspace` which showed workspace and workspace-archive. But now `ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` returns content. Maybe there's a sudo issue or something changed.\n\n\nActually, I just realized I was running `ls -la ~/.openclaw/` as the user, not as sudo, so permissions should be consistent. Let me look back at what that output actually showed me - I need to trace through the actual results to understand why workspace-tts wasn't visible before but exists now.\n","thinkingSignature":"07557332f5679243f3f1018ebde98b71dd17156df2cd64b2adb2a7be1bb7bf88"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_e9h4bp0mu904_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la /home/halei/.openclaw/ | grep workspace","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":86,"output":292,"cacheRead":64481,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":64859,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780057277624,"responseId":"0668b7be16a862962f885c10e3af5561"}}
{"type":"message","id":"13a58150","parentId":"0fc11c14","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:21:24.552Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_e9h4bp0mu904_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"drwx------ 50 halei halei     4096  5月 29 03:00 workspace\ndrwxrwxr-x  5 halei halei     4096  5月 10 15:19 workspace-archive-e-commerce"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":63,"aggregated":"drwx------ 50 halei halei     4096  5月 29 03:00 workspace\ndrwxrwxr-x  5 halei halei     4096  5月 10 15:19 workspace-archive-e-commerce","cwd":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1780057284520}}
{"type":"message","id":"3fd8dbc3","parentId":"13a58150","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:21:34.736Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Interesting! So:\n- `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` exists (ls -la showed it earlier)\n- But `~/.openclaw/` listing doesn't show it!\n\nWait, the first command showed `workspace-tts/` with `drwx------  8 halei`. But the second command only shows `workspace` and `workspace-archive-e-commerce`. Something is very off here.\n\nOh wait - let me look at the first ls output again:\n```\n/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace:\ntotal 11432\n...\n```\n\nAh, that was `~/.openclaw/workspace/` not `~/.openclaw/`. \n\nSo the actual `.openclaw` directory contains just `workspace` and `workspace-archive-e-commerce`. There's no `workspace-tts` subdirectory in `.openclaw` itself. Meanwhile, in the home directory there's a `workspace-tts/` folder at `~/workspace-tts`. So the backup script is trying to rsync `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` which doesn't exist - that's the problem.\n\nThe `do_rsync` function only copies something if the source path exists, so when the script tries to backup `workspace-tts/` from `.openclaw`, it skips it entirely. The actual workspace content is living in `~/workspace-tts/` instead, which is a separate directory entirely.\n\nThe backup is looking in the wrong location—it's checking `.openclaw/workspace-tts/` when the files are actually at `~/workspace-tts/`. That's why the backup is missing the TTS workspace entirely. I need to correct the backup configuration to point to the right directory.\n","thinkingSignature":"da4d6fee24c29eef48a42df252daf806b4bb87a127bf2f12c6442f21cd9094a0"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到问题了。备份脚本在漏东西——\n\n备份写的是：\n```bash\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"\n```\n\n但 `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` 这个路径根本不存在（上面 ls 验证过了）。TTS 的 workspace 实际在 `~/workspace-tts/`，不是 `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/`。\n\n这就是为什么备份里没有 TTS。我来修复备份脚本：\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_jiick8o06dh0_1","name":"read","arguments":{"path":"/home/halei/.openclaw/workspace/skills/openclaw-backup/backup.sh"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":120,"output":471,"cacheRead":64564,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":65155,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780057285201,"responseId":"0668b7c50c4acc0c237d782d4ac07cf9"}}
{"type":"message","id":"5cdace41","parentId":"3fd8dbc3","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:21:34.857Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_jiick8o06dh0_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"#!/bin/bash\n# OpenClaw Daily Backup Script (v3.1 — 2026-04-21)\n# 只做备份，不跑 evolver\n\nBACKUP_REPO=\"/tmp/openclaw-backup-clone\"\nOPENCLAW_DIR=\"$HOME/.openclaw\"\nGIT_REF=\"main\"\nDATE_DIR=$(date '+%Y-%m-%d')\n\nGH_TOKEN=*** \"oauth_token:\" ~/.config/gh/hosts.yml | awk '{print $2}')\n\necho \"[$(date)] Starting OpenClaw backup...\"\n\n# Clone or update backup repo\nif [ -d \"$BACKUP_REPO/.git\" ]; then\n  cd \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\n  git checkout \"$GIT_REF\" 2>/dev/null\n  git pull origin \"$GIT_REF\" --quiet\nelse\n  rm -rf \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\n  git clone \"https://${GH_TOKEN}@github.com/59330857/openclaw-backup.git\" \"$BACKUP_REPO\" --quiet\nfi\n\n# Fresh date dir (replace old snapshot entirely)\nrm -rf \"$BACKUP_REPO/$DATE_DIR\"\nmkdir -p \"$BACKUP_REPO/$DATE_DIR\"\n\n# rsync helper: dest always inside $DATE_DIR/\ndo_rsync() {\n  local src=\"$1\"\n  local dst=\"$2\"   # relative to $DATE_DIR/\n  if [ -e \"$src\" ]; then\n    rsync -a --exclude='.git' \"$src\" \"$BACKUP_REPO/$DATE_DIR/$dst\"\n  fi\n}\n\n# 1. Core config files (no trailing slash = copy as file)\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw.json\" \"\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw.json.bak\" \"\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw.json.bak.1\" \"\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openviking.env\" \"\"\n\n# 2. Directories (trailing slash = copy contents)\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/agents/\" \"agents/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/credentials/\" \"credentials/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/cron/\" \"cron/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/devices/\" \"devices/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/flows/\" \"flows/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/identity/\" \"identity/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/feishu/\" \"feishu/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/subagents/\" \"subagents/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/extensions/\" \"extensions/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/skills/\" \"skills/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace/\" \"workspace/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-agent-orchestrator/\" \"workspace-agent-orchestrator/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-main/\" \"workspace-main/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-content/\" \"workspace-content/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-koc/\" \"workspace-koc/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-traffic/\" \"workspace-traffic/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-ops/\" \"workspace-ops/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-director/\" \"workspace-director/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-finance/\" \"workspace-finance/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-review/\" \"workspace-review/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/memory/\" \"memory/\"\ndo_rsync \"$HOME/.evomap/\" \"evomap/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/qqbot/\" \"qqbot/\"\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/openclaw-weixin/\" \"openclaw-weixin/\"\n\n# Commit and push\ncd \"$BACKUP_REPO\"\nif [ -n \"$(git status --porcelain)\" ]; then\n  git config user.email \"backup@openclaw\"\n  git config user.name \"OpenClaw Backup\"\n  git add -A\n  git commit -m \"Full backup $DATE_DIR $(date '+%H:%M')\"\n  git push origin \"$GIT_REF\"\n  echo \"[$(date)] Backup pushed to GitHub\"\n\n  # ── Send Feishu notification ──────────────────────────────────────\n  SCRIPT_DIR=\"$(cd \"$(dirname \"$0\")\" && pwd)\"\n  node \"$SCRIPT_DIR/send-to-me.js\" \"✅ 每日备份完成\\n📦 备份 → 已推送至 openclaw-backup\" && echo \"[$(date)] Backup Feishu notification sent\" || echo \"[$(date)] Failed to send Feishu notification\"\n  # ── End Feishu notification ────────────────────────────────────────\nelse\n  echo \"[$(date)] No changes, skipping commit\"\nfi\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1780057294856}}
{"type":"message","id":"6e4c859b","parentId":"5cdace41","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:21:53.043Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I see - the backup script says `do_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"` where `OPENCLAW_DIR=\"$HOME/.openclaw\"`. So it's trying to rsync from `$HOME/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` to `$BACKUP_REPO/$DATE_DIR/workspace-tts/`.\n\nBut:\n- `$HOME/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` doesn't exist\n- `~/workspace-tts/` does exist\n\nSo the rsync command silently failed (because `do_rsync` checks `if [ -e \"$src\" ]` and the source doesn't exist).\n\n\nThe backup script should be using `$HOME/workspace-tts/` instead, and I'm also noticing the workspace-selector directory that appears in the workspace folder isn't being backed up either, even though it was mentioned earlier.\n\nLooking at the backup logs, I can see workspace-tts was already present in the May 10 backup, so this is a long-standing issue where the script has been referencing the wrong path.\n\nThe real problem is that `do_rsync` silently skips non-existent directories because of the `if [ -e \"$src\" ]` check, so workspace-tts never gets backed up even though the source location is wrong. I need to fix the backup script to use the correct path for workspace-tts and also ensure workspace-selector gets included in the backup.\n","thinkingSignature":"2fe7f5d768d9a257160f488028257f79da0ed0b554e61b8d00f311585a2642c9"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\n找到问题了。备份脚本里写的是：\n\n```bash\ndo_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"\n# 其中 OPENCLAW_DIR=\"$HOME/.openclaw\"\n# 所以实际路径是 ~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/\n```\n\n但 `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` **不存在**！`workspace-tts` 实际在 `~/workspace-tts/`。\n\n因为 `do_rsync` 里检查了 `if [ -e \"$src\" ]`，源目录不存在就跳过了，所以 workspace-tts 一直没被备份。\n\n需要修复两处：\n1. **workspace-tts** → 应该是 `$HOME/workspace-tts/`（不是 `$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/`）\n2. **workspace-selector** → 也缺失，没有被备份\n\n要我帮你修复备份脚本吗？修复后下次（明天凌晨）备份就会包含这些 workspace。"}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":1062,"output":476,"cacheRead":64681,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":66219,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1780057296725,"responseId":"0668b7d1d3ee62ee2ef814ca5d091ce1"}}
