{"type":"message","id":"c0184cfe","parentId":"c4a08958","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:22:51.119Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user is saying \"selector删除不，不是改为tts了吗\" - which seems to mean \"wasn't selector changed to tts?\" They seem confused about why there's still a \"workspace-tts\" being mentioned when the workspace-tts was already replaced/renamed from something else.\n\nLet me look at what exists now and understand the situation better. The user might be referring to a previous team structure where there was a \"selector\" agent that got replaced with \"tts\". Let me check what's actually in the backup.\n\nActually looking back at the backup content list:\n```\nworkspace\nworkspace-content\nworkspace-director\nworkspace-finance\nworkspace-koc\n\n\nworkspace-ops\nworkspace-review\nworkspace-traffic\n```\n\nI notice \"selector\" isn't there at all - it's not in the backup or current workspaces. But the backup script is using the wrong path for workspace-tts, so it's been silently failing to back it up. The user seems to know about this misconfiguration already. I need to figure out which workspaces are actually missing their backups.\n\nLooking at the backup log more carefully, I see the script is checking for workspace-tts but using the wrong directory path. And when I look at what's actually been backed up, workspace-selector and workspace-main are also missing. The user's comment about \"selector不是改为tts了吗\" suggests they know selector was replaced with tts, but I need to understand what other workspaces might be misconfigured in the script.\n\nI think I need to just confirm with the user which workspaces aren't getting backed up and ask if they want me to fix the backup paths.\n","thinkingSignature":"6e608066ef4246ecaae410d08cc3524cb51a7938e9d85dc51d09ff54a32db690"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_egqepxpiilta_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls ~/workspace* 2>/dev/null; echo \"---\"; ls ~/.openclaw