{"type":"message","id":"9af019b0","parentId":"8580485c","timestamp":"2026-05-29T12:23:05.872Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand. Looking at the current workspaces:\n\nIn `~/.openclaw/workspace/`:\n- `workspace` (the main KIIT workspace)\n- `workspace-main`\n- `workspace-selector`\n- `workspace-tts`\n\nIn `$HOME/`:\n- `workspace-agent-orchestrator`\n- `workspace-content`\n- `workspace-director`\n- `workspace-finance`\n- `workspace-koc`\n- `workspace-ops`\n- `workspace-review`\n- `workspace-traffic`\n- `workspace-tts`\n- `workspace` (with clawport-ui)\n\nThe backup script has:\n- `do_rsync \"$OPENCLAW_DIR/workspace-tts/\" \"workspace-tts/\"` → looks for `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` which DOES exist\n\n\n- `do_rsync \"$HOME/workspace-content/\" \"workspace-content/\"` → looks for `~/workspace-content/` which exists\n- etc.\n\nSo `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` exists and should be backed up. But I checked earlier and it returned no output, which is strange because the directory clearly exists now.\n\nWait, I'm seeing `workspace-tts` in both locations - one at `~/.openclaw/workspace-tts/` and another at `~/workspace-tts/`. When I ran `ls -la ~/.openclaw/ | grep workspace` earlier, it only showed `workspace` and `workspace-archive-e-commerce`, not `workspace-tts`. But now I'm seeing it in the output. This is confusing - let me look more carefully at what the user is actually asking about workspaces and what's happening with the selector.\n\nLooking at the backup script, I notice there's no rsync entry for `workspace-selector` - it's missing from the backup configuration entirely. The script has entries for `workspace-tts`, `workspace-agent-orchestrator`, and `workspace-main`, but `workspace-selector` isn't listed anywhere. That's the issue - it's not being backed up.\n\nThe user mentioned \"selector删除不,不是改为tts了吗\" - they're asking if selector was deleted and replaced by tts. Looking at the directories, I can see `workspace-tts` exists, but `workspace-selector` is still there too. It seems like the selector wasn't actually removed, just renamed or supplemented with tts, so both directories exist in the backup when maybe only one should.\n","thinkingSignature":"a65065a948e12b472ed7b3bf23a6846deeb87e10a456b91286ffe5ca82443a7e"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_ov6oy0kekjmk_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"ls -la ~/.openclaw/workspace/ | grep -E \"selector|tts\"","timeout":5}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":485,"output":532,"cacheRead":66228,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":67245,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1780057371404,"responseId":"0668b81b81c1d8fd52c29a9ca957229b"}}
